    <note>Luo(2) Zhongshu [16450] Hunan TZ, 134.3a; Guangdong TZ, 66.6a. Listed as both a Lianzhou (Guangdong) and Guiyang jinshi. Lianzhou becomes Guiyang fu, which had its seat located in Guiyang county [modern Lianxian]) and is situated continguuous with Linwu county (est. 1141) of Guiyang jun in Hunan. Although the Hunan TZ provides couunty identification, I am treating this Luo as a Lianzhou, Guiyang county lineage because of citatations of two earlier local histories in the Guangdong TZ as well as the anachronistic identification of Linwu as the county of residence.</note>
